---
description: AI cost-control and provider-routing rules
alwaysApply: true
---

Every AI call must go through the AI router.

Do not call provider SDKs directly from route handlers.

Every AI request must include:
- provider
- model
- module_name
- job_id
- max_input_tokens
- max_output_tokens
- temperature
- timeout_seconds
- max_retries
- cost_ceiling_credits
- fallback_provider
- fallback_model

Every response must log:
- provider
- model
- module_name
- job_id
- input_tokens_estimated
- output_tokens_reported_or_estimated
- latency_ms
- success/failure
- retry_count
- cost_estimate
- rate_limit_headers if available

If a job would exceed customer credits, do not start the job.

If an AI module would exceed the per-job budget, fail safe and return a structured error.
